ources using the MacOSVM custom resource definition.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/MLWorkloads":{"title":"Machine Learning Workloads","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/mlworkloads","abstract":[{"text":"Run ML training and inference on Apple Silicon GPUs inside Spooktacular virtual machines.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/OpenClawGuide":{"title":"Running OpenClaw in Virtual Machines","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/openclawguide","abstract":[{"text":"Run two isolated OpenClaw AI agent instances on a single Mac — each with its own workspace, channels, and API keys.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/Versioning":{"title":"Versioning & Release Schedule","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/versioning","abstract":[{"text":"Understand what version numbers mean and what to expect from each release.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","title":"SpooktacularKit","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create and manage macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/RemoteDesktop":{"title":"Remote Desktop Access","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/spooktac